                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2507.</note>
                <head>[Telegram–Paraphrase.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nuevo Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Forty-five rifles and 20,000 cartridges captured to-day by commander of Fort
                    McIntosh, also a lieutenant in the revolutionary army, who states he is
                    commissioned by Gen. Reyes personally.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
